Step 1: Calculate Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100
• From the income statement:
  Gross Profit = 4,788,736.33
  Total Revenue = 16,388,736.33
• Calculation: (4,788,736.33 ÷ 16,388,736.33) × 100 ≈ 29.23%

Step 2: Calculate Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities ÷ Total Current Liabilities
• From the cash flow statement and balance sheet:
  Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -6,316,405.44
  Total Current Liabilities = 4,319,436.82
• Calculation: -6,316,405.44 ÷ 4,319,436.82 ≈ -1.46

Thus, the solution is:
{"solution": {"Gross Profit Margin": "29.23%", "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-1.46"}}
